  "name": "Morrison COU1 — CPB hemolysis credibility assessment (environmental gap variant)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under cardiopulmonary bypass (CPB) conditions. COU1 evaluates whether the computational model can identify worst-case hemolysis operating conditions for a Class II CPB device at Model Risk Level 2. The pump is deployed in operating-room environments where ambient temperature can drift between 18°C and 26°C, electromagnetic interference from surgical equipment is present, and altitude-dependent ambient pressure variations of ±8 kPa are observed in facilities at elevation. Despite this, all validation experiments were conducted under fixed laboratory conditions (22°C, 1 atm, EMI-shielded room). No environmental sensitivity study has been performed, and the operating envelope does not formally bound these environmental parameters. Full 13-factor assessment: 7 factors assessed (all meeting required levels), 6 factors not assessed (acceptable at MRL 2).",
  "assuranceLevel": "Medium",
  "couName": "CPB use",
  "decision": "Accepted",
  "deviceClass": "Class II",
  "modelRiskLevel": 2,
  "bindsRequirement": "https://uofa.net/synth/req/morrison-cpb-hemolysis-rhl-criterion",
  "bindsClaim": "https://uofa.net/synth/claim/morrison-cpb-cfd-hemolysis-worst-case",
