      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Relative hemolysis index validation across 5 operating points",
      "description": "Hemolysis index measurements performed in bench-top loop at 22°C, 101.3 kPa, with no electromagnetic interference sources present. RH values predicted by CFD compared against measured normalized index of hemolysis (NIH). All five operating points yielded RH < 1 relative to predicate. Laboratory conditions held constant throughout; no variation in temperature, pressure, or EMI environment was introduced or studied.",
      "outcome": "Passed",
      "quantitativeResult": "RH range: 0.61–0.89 across all 5 operating points (criterion: RH < 1)"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/synth/validation/morrison-vr-03-wall-shear-stress",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Wall shear stress distribution comparison",
